03/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Greece and Turkey will activate the so-called "2+2" formula, which provides for joint backing of Macedonia and Albania's NATO and EU aspirations. Greek Deputy Defence Minister Lazaros Lotidis announced the move during his Thursday (2 January) visit to Tirana. Greece and Turkey first launched the "2+2" co-operation initiative to assist Bulgaria and Romania's Euro-Atlantic efforts. (A1 TV - 02/01/03)
